cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MS 

The paper is about game theory, specifically incomplete information games with uncertainty in the payoff matrix. This falls under the category of cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses distributionally robust optimization, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization, falling under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The computational methods used to compute equilibria involve solving a system of equations and inequalities, which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.MS (Mathematical Software).
